Q. You're trying to find the mean number of items per order on Alibaba, rounded to 1 decimal place using tables which includes information 
on the count of items in each order (item_count table) and the corresponding number of orders for each item count (order_occurrences table).

A. 
Method 1:
SELECT ROUND(
  (SUM(ITEM_COUNT::DECIMAL * ORDER_OCCURRENCES)/SUM(ORDER_OCCURRENCES)), 
1) as mean
FROM items_per_order;

Method 2(using CTE function):
WITH TOTALS AS (
  SELECT SUM(ITEM_COUNT::DECIMAL * ORDER_OCCURRENCES) AS TOTAL_ITEM,
  SUM(ORDER_OCCURRENCES) AS TOTAL_ORDER
  FROM items_per_order
)

SELECT ROUND(TOTAL_ITEM * 1.0/TOTAL_ORDER, 1) AS MEAN
FROM TOTALS;
